# ABSOLUTE BAN ON git push

## THE RULE (non-negotiable)

**NEVER run `git push` or any command that pushes to remote** unless the user explicitly says one of:
- "push"
- "push it"
- "now push"
- or any other clear direct instruction to push

## What you CAN do without asking

- `git add`
- `git commit`
- Any local git operations

## What requires EXPLICIT user instruction

- `git push` — NEVER do this on your own
- `git push --force` — NEVER
- Any `gh` command that pushes or publishes

## Why

This is a production site with 1M+ monthly visitors. Unauthorized pushes go live immediately and can break things for real users.
